## How to set up repo

### Prerequisites

* Install terraform
    * Install [CLI here](https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/install)
    * Install Terraform extension for VS Code


### Create repo

Create a new Github repo:
* Set `my-repo-name` to `infrastructure`
* Repo must be part of an organization `my-organization-name` (i.e. not a personal repo)
    * Create an organization if you don't have one yet
    * Existing personal repos can be transferred to an organization as long as you have `admin` privledges
        * Go to your repo Settings > General > Danger Zone > Transfer ownership
    * Set Workflow permissions in BOTH the organization AND repo
        * Navigate to organization > Settings > Actions (left column) > General
            * Select "Read and write permissions"
            * Check "Allow GitHub Actions to create and approve pull requests"
        * Do the same for your repo

#### Architecture

infrastructure/
├── api-server/
│   ├── terraform/
│   │   ├── main.tf          # Your existing EC2 config
│   │   └── variables.tf
│   └── .github/workflows/
│       └── deploy.yml       # Your existing API deployment
│
├── bot-platform/
│   ├── terraform/
│   │   ├── main.tf          # New multi-bot infrastructure
│   │   └── variables.tf
│   └── template/            # Bot template for teams
│       └── .github/workflows/
│           └── deploy.yml
│
├── shared/
│   └── terraform/
│       ├── main.tf          # Shared resources (VPC, subnets)
│       └── outputs.tf       # Exported values for both services
│
└── terraform.tf             # Root config linking all modules

